data.name: bOpen.ToolTip
data.value:
Open the archive with a third-party software.
If 7zip is installed, this will open the archive using it's file manager. Otherwise it will fall back on opening it with windows explorer.
You can change what software to launch in the settings.

data.name: bWorkingArea.ToolTip
data.value:
Extract archive contents to working area folder.
Working area folders are used as a temporary storage area for things you are working on, so that you dont have to make decisions about location and naming. Example:
Foo.zip contains a single folder "bar" with some contents. Working area base is c:\Work and the current area number is 4 The contents will be located in C:\Work\004\bar
